<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,223,249]" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">Remarks.</emphasis>
As mentioned above, this widespread species was the first to be published from 
<collectingCountry box="[1198,1321,223,249]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Klapalek, F." pageId="16" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 193" refId="ref13935" refString="Klapalek, F. (1923) Plecopteres II. Fam. Perlidae. Subfam. Perlinae, Subfam. Neoperlinae. Collections Zoologiques du Baron Edm. de Selys Longchamps, 4 (2), 1 - 193." type="journal article" year="1923">Klapálek 1923</bibRefCitation>
). Though the latest review of the genus suggests that species identification can be possible only on the basis of eggs (
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P." box="[217,443,295,321]" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref14690" refString="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P. (2002) The species of Perla (Plecoptera: Perlidae): evidence from egg morphology. Scopolia, 49, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="2002">Sivec &amp; Stark 2002</bibRefCitation>
), our larvae agrees well with its recent description from the Greater Caucasus (
<bibRefCitation author="Zhiltzova, L. A. &amp; Cherchesova, S." pageId="16" pageNumber="74" pagination="321 - 326" refId="ref15605" refString="Zhiltzova, L. A. &amp; Cherchesova, S. K (2003) Description of the larva of genus Perla Geoff. (Plecoptera, Perlidae) from the Caucasus. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie, 82 (2), 321 - 326. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="2003">Zhiltzova &amp; Cherchesova 2003</bibRefCitation>
), and compared with our Georgian specimens that are containing matured eggs. Our 
<collectingCountry name="Azerbaijan" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
specimens were caught in both large and small forest streams of different elevations.
</paragraph>
